**Question 1.7.1**


When we have multiple groups itâ€™s easier for us to see the differences when we change point colour and shape. However, at some point there are too many groups to keep things straight. We are approaching that on the plot above, and so we need to do something different. One thing we could try is to change the point to a line to reduce the noise/chaos of the plot above. We would also not have a shape. Do that in the cell below and name the plot object `polio_regions_line`.



```{r q1_7_1, echo=TRUE, exercise=TRUE, exercise.lines = 6, exercise.setup = "world_vacc-setup"}





